<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Weather App</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="/img/weather.png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css" />
    <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/b1a8a7536f.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>

<body class="">
    <div class='flex flex-col min-h-screen bg-color-one text-colorT-one'>
        {{>header}}
        <main class='bg-color-two flex-grow flex'>
            <div class="mx-4 sm:mx-8 lg:mx-16 my-2 sm:my-6 lg:my-8 ">
                <h1 class="text-center uppercase text-xl sm:text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold">{{title}}</h1>
                <img class="h-40 sm:h-48 md:h-56 lg:h-64 w-full object-contain mt-4 mb-6 sm:mb-8 md:mb-12 lg:mb-16"
                    src="/img/whatHappened.jpeg" alt="picture of maria del carmen from santiagocodes" />
                <div class="leading-7 lg:text-xl leading-relaxed lg:leading-loose">
                    <p class='font-semibold'>What is this webpage?</p>
                    <p>This is a very basic webpage that tells users about the weather in any location in the world.</p>
                    <br>
                    <p class='font-semibold'>How does it work?</p>
                    <p>It's very simple. Click on the 'weather' tab. On this page the user will find an input box where
                        he/she can type in the location they want. Click the 'search' button beside the input box and
                        voil√†!
                    </p>
                    <br>
                    <p class='font-semibold'>I followed the instructions, but got the weather information from some
                        other
                        place. What can I do?</p>
                    <p>I suggest users be more specific with their queries. What does this mean? Don't just
                        type in the city name, try typing in the country's name as well.</p>
                    <br>
                    <p class='font-semibold'>Are you a fellow developer?</p>
                    <p>If you are a developer and want to take a look at the code you can do so <a
                            class='underline hover:text-colorT-three'
                            href="https://github.com/santiagocodes/node-udemy-course">here</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </main>
        {{>footer}}
    </div>
    <script src="./js/app.js"></script>
</body>

</html>